---
description: Git command execution safety rules
globs: ["src-tauri/src/**/*.rs"]
alwaysApply: true
---

All Git commands must be safe, explicit, and testable.

Rules:
- never interpolate shell strings with user input
- always pass args as a structured argument array
- always set current_dir for repository operations
- prefer machine-readable Git output
- use timeouts for long-running commands when appropriate
- capture stdout and stderr separately
- normalize and validate paths
- do not assume path separator behavior across macOS and Windows

Command design:
- executor builds and runs commands
- parsers transform stdout into typed models
- services map results/errors into application-level contracts

Preferred Git patterns:
- porcelain output for status
- explicit delimiters for log parsing
- separate commands for staged and unstaged diff
- branch/ref queries with structured format where possible

Do not:
- parse UI-facing human-readable output if a machine-friendly mode exists
- mix command construction and parsing in the same function
- return raw process output directly to the frontend